article.headline: Campbell 88, Longwood 80
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Jonathan Rodriguez scored 25 points as Campbell defeated Longwood 88-80 Thursday night. The Fighting Camels (12-16) made 14 of their first 18 shots and went 5-of-7 on 3-pointers in the second half, leading by as many as 25 at 80-55 before the Lancers (9-21) closed the gap down the stretch. Rodriguez finished 8-of-13 from the field and 9-of-12 from the line. Campbell led 43-38 with 18:14 left in the game, then went on a 17-2 run to take a 20-point lead. The Camels led 84-64 with 3:24 left before Longwood ended the game with a 16-4 run. Ledell Eackles scored 13 points for Campbell, all in the second half, and Eric Smith had 12. Clayton Morgan led Longwood with 27 points and 11 rebounds before fouling out late in the game. Morgan hit 11-of-19 from the floor and 5-of-8 from the free throw line. Maurice Sumter added 18 points, while Brandon Giles had 10.
